article.headline: George Washington 83, Richmond 65
article.story: WASHINGTON -- Lasan Kromah matched his career-high with 25 points and Tony Taylor scored 21 points as George Washington routed Richmond 83-65 Wednesday night. The Colonials (7-11, 2-2 Atlantic 10 Conference) shot 69.2 percent in the second half, 58.2 percent overall (32 of 55) and took control with an 18-3 run midway through the game. Kromah scored 16 points after halftime, knocking down all seven of his second half shots and 11 of 15 attempts overall. After letting a 10-point lead in the first half disappear, the Colonials entered halftime on a 9-2 run for a 33-27 advantage, the final six points coming from Taylor. Kromah accounted for the first four points of the second half as a 9-1 push coming out of intermission extended the lead to 42-28. The Colonials led by 23 points in the closing minutes. Darien Brothers scored 17 points to lead the Spiders (11-8, 2-2).
